    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Mass Assignment Protection</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">Scaffolded controllers include built-in mass assignment protection to prevent security vulnerabilities. The <code>_permit_params</code> method whitelists only the allowed fields:</p>

    <div class="mb-8 rounded-xl bg-gray-900/50 border border-white/10 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-3 bg-white/5 border-b border-white/10">
            <span class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-400">Security Pattern</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <pre class="text-sm leading-7"><code class="language-soli"><span class="text-purple-400">class</span> <span class="text-yellow-200">UsersController</span> <span class="text-purple-400">&lt;</span> <span class="text-yellow-200">Controller</span> {
    <span class="text-gray-500">// POST /users</span>
    <span class="text-purple-400">def</span> <span class="text-blue-400">create</span>(req: <span class="text-yellow-200">Any</span>) -> <span class="text-yellow-200">Any</span> {
        <span class="text-gray-500">// Only permit whitelisted fields</span>
        <span class="text-purple-400">let</span> permitted = <span class="text-purple-400">this</span>._permit_params(req[<span class="text-green-400">"params"</span>]);
        <span class="text-purple-400">let</span> result = <span class="text-yellow-200">Users</span>.<span class="text-blue-400">create</span>(permitted);
        <span class="text-gray-500">// ...</span>
    }

    <span class="text-gray-500">// Mass assignment protection</span>
    <span class="text-purple-400">def</span> <span class="text-blue-400">_permit_params</span>(params: <span class="text-yellow-200">Any</span>) -> <span class="text-yellow-200">Any</span> {
        {
            <span class="text-green-400">"name"</span>: params[<span class="text-green-400">"name"</span>],
            <span class="text-green-400">"email"</span>: params[<span class="text-green-400">"email"</span>]
        }
    }
}</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-yellow-500/10 border border-yellow-500/20 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-400 mb-2">Security Best Practice</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-yellow-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
                </svg>
                Never pass raw <code class="mx-1 text-yellow-300">req.params</code> directly to model operations
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-yellow-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
                </svg>
                Always use <code class="mx-1 text-yellow-300">_permit_params()</code> to filter input
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-yellow-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
                </svg>
                Add sensitive fields (is_admin, role, permissions) to the blacklist if needed
            </li>
        </ul>
